descript.abstract: This version utilizes a generalized boundary along the coast, which is sometimes necessary for analysis in which it is important to encompass segments of roadways that travel over water. Roadways on bridges or causeways that span intracoastal waterways are not covered by detailed polygons that precisely follow the coastline, therefore a generalized boundary is needed for some types of analysis where it is important to preserve such relationships. Date valid as of: February 2015 Publish Date: February 2015 Update Frequency: Infrequently, as needed.
descript.purpose: TxDOT county layer. This version utilizes a generalized boundary along the coast.
